Dataset
The project uses the MovieLens Latest Dataset (ml-latest/), which includes:

movies.csv â†’ Movie details (title, genres)

ratings.csv â†’ User ratings for movies

tags.csv â†’ User-provided tags for movies

links.csv â†’ External identifiers (IMDb, TMDb)

Installation
Requirements
Python 3.8+

Libraries:

bash
pip install numpy pandas matplotlib seaborn scikit-learn
Run 
Download MovieLens dataset and place files in ml-latest/ directory.

Run the script in Jupyter Notebook or Python IDE:

bash
python recommender.py

Project Workflow
Data Preparation

Load datasets

Inspect shape and head of each file

Feature Engineering

Extract userId and movieId as features

Use rating as target variable

Model Training & Evaluation

Train Linear Regression, Decision Tree, and KNN models

Evaluate using RMSE and RÂ²

Select best model

Recommendation Generation

Identify unseen movies for a user

Predict ratings using trained model

Select top 10 recommendations

Result Integration

